Automation scripts
==================

This directory is for scripts that automate sequences of trap
interactions — moving traps along paths, running protocols, or
coordinating trap arrays over time.

Hooks for automation
--------------------

The trap infrastructure exposes several signals suitable for driving
automation:

- ``QTrap.changed`` — emitted whenever a trap's position or properties
  change; connect to update downstream state.
- ``QTrapArray.reshaping`` / ``QTrapArray.reshaped`` — bracket a
  repopulation event; useful for pausing computations while the array
  is being rebuilt.
- ``QTrapOverlay.trapAdded`` / ``QTrapOverlay.trapRemoved`` — fired
  when traps enter or leave the overlay; useful for bookkeeping.

Walking traps
-------------

``QTrapGroup.leaves()`` returns an iterator over every individual
``QTweezer`` (or other leaf trap) in a group, regardless of nesting
depth. Use this to apply a position update uniformly across a
structured trap such as a ``QTextArray``.

Example skeleton
----------------

.. code-block:: python

    from QFab.lib.traps.QTrapOverlay import QTrapOverlay

    def move_all_to(overlay: QTrapOverlay, x: float, y: float) -> None:
        for trap in list(overlay.leaves()):
            trap.r = (x, y, trap.r[2])
